Outstanding red Burgundies of the great years of 1961 and 1959 are hard to come by. Practically none exist in the cellars of Burgundy. These four thoroughbreds have been nurtured to their present excellence and maturity under the loving and knowledgeable care of Monsieur Trinquet, a distinguished wine authority who has been head of the Vinicultural School of Beaune for some 30 years. His pupils include practically all the top vintners who are making wine in Burgundy today.

As further testimony of the excellence, is the fact that Frank Schoonmaker tasted these wines, found them outstanding, and he proved to be sufficiently persuasive to be able to acquire them. They are now resting quietly in our cellars to bring their vinous joy to you. 7
